================================================================================
INTEGRITY ISSUES — Git Hygiene, Exposed Files & Push Safety
================================================================================
Audit of tracked files, .gitignore coverage, and runtime data leaking into VCS.
Goal: clean `git status` before pushes, no personal/runtime data in the repo.
================================================================================


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CATEGORY 1 — COMPILED / CACHE FILES TRACKED IN GIT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[INT-001] 13 PYTHON __pycache__/*.pyc FILES ARE TRACKED
  Path: agentin/plugins/http-tts-bridge/python_backend/backend/__pycache__/
        agentin/plugins/http-tts-bridge/python_backend/backend/routers/__pycache__/
  These are compiled bytecode files that change on every Python run and are
  machine-specific. They should never be in VCS.
  Files:
    __init__.cpython-311.pyc     app.cpython-311.pyc
    catalog.cpython-311.pyc      config.cpython-311.pyc
    models.cpython-311.pyc       stability.cpython-311.pyc
    state.cpython-311.pyc        tts_engine.cpython-311.pyc
    voice_cloner.cpython-311.pyc voice_preparer.cpython-311.pyc
    routers/agent.cpython-311.pyc  routers/system.cpython-311.pyc
    routers/voices.cpython-311.pyc

  Fix — add to .gitignore and untrack:
    # In .gitignore:
    __pycache__/
    *.pyc

    # Then run:
    git rm -r --cached agentin/plugins/http-tts-bridge/python_backend/backend/__pycache__/
    git rm -r --cached agentin/plugins/http-tts-bridge/python_backend/backend/routers/__pycache__/


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CATEGORY 2 — RUNTIME-GENERATED DATA TRACKED IN GIT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[INT-002] A2A EVENT LOGS AND TASK STATE — 21 files tracked
  Path: agentin/a2a/events/*.jsonl  (9 files)
        agentin/a2a/tasks/*.json    (9 files)
        agentin/a2a/targets/*.json  (3 files: codex.json, comfyui.json, lmstudio.json)
  The events/ and tasks/ directories contain runtime-generated session data with
  UUIDs. These change every time A2A tasks run and will constantly dirty git status.
  The targets/ files (codex.json, comfyui.json, lmstudio.json) may be intentional
  config — decide if they're templates or runtime state.

  Fix — add to .gitignore and untrack:
    agentin/a2a/events/
    agentin/a2a/tasks/
    # If targets are also runtime-generated:
    # agentin/a2a/targets/

    git rm -r --cached agentin/a2a/events/
    git rm -r --cached agentin/a2a/tasks/

[INT-003] SUB-AGENT DEFINITIONS WITH TIMESTAMP IDs — 8 runtime sub-agents
  Path: agentin/agents/sub/
  Tracked files include runtime-spawned sub-agents with timestamp-based names:
    diag-search-1776453748776/system.md
    live-search-verifier-1776453564659/system.md
    live-search-verifier-1776453628736/system.md
    live-time-verifier-1776454130153/system.md
    live-time-verifier-1776454985119/system.md
    live-time-verifier-1776455978209/system.md
    live-time-verifier-1776457715692/system.md
  These are ephemeral sub-agents created during sessions. Each new run creates
  new ones, dirtying git status. Only template sub-agents should be tracked
  (live-subagent, outcome-agent, reminder-agent, search-agent).

  Fix — add to .gitignore and untrack the timestamped ones:
    # Ignore runtime-spawned sub-agents (contain timestamps in folder name)
    agentin/agents/sub/diag-*/
    agentin/agents/sub/live-search-verifier-*/
    agentin/agents/sub/live-time-verifier-*/
    # OR broader: ignore all sub-agents except templates
    # agentin/agents/sub/*/
    # !agentin/agents/sub/live-subagent/
    # !agentin/agents/sub/outcome-agent/
    # !agentin/agents/sub/reminder-agent/
    # !agentin/agents/sub/search-agent/

    git rm -r --cached agentin/agents/sub/diag-search-1776453748776/
    git rm -r --cached agentin/agents/sub/live-search-verifier-*/
    git rm -r --cached agentin/agents/sub/live-time-verifier-*/

[INT-004] WORKFLOW DEFINITIONS — mixed template vs runtime
  Path: agentin/workflows/
  Tracked files:
    live_workflow_test.json       ← runtime test artifact
    morning_briefing.json         ← likely a template (keep)
    quick_web_research.json       ← likely a template (keep)
    system_health_check.json      ← likely a template (keep)
    system_health_check_copy.json ← accidental copy/duplicate
    workflow.md                   ← documentation (keep)
    runs/.gitignore               ← correct

  Fix:
    - Delete system_health_check_copy.json (duplicate)
    - Decide if live_workflow_test.json should be tracked or ignored
    - If workflows are user-created at runtime, ignore *.json:
      agentin/workflows/*.json
      !agentin/workflows/morning_briefing.json
      !agentin/workflows/quick_web_research.json
      !agentin/workflows/system_health_check.json

[INT-005] TASKS.MD — runtime task queue snapshot
  Path: agentin/tasks/tasks.md
  This appears to be a runtime-written file that the daemon updates with
  current task state. It will change on every daemon tick and dirty git.

  Fix:
    agentin/tasks/


