CATEGORY 3 — AGENT RUNTIME STATE PARTIALLY IGNORED
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[INT-006] PRO AGENT state.json IGNORED BUT state.default.json TRACKED
  .gitignore has:
    agentin/agents/pro/*/config/state.json
  But this file is tracked:
    agentin/agents/pro/background-daemon/config/state.default.json
  This is actually correct — state.default.json is a template, state.json is
  runtime. No action needed, just documenting the pattern for clarity.
  ✅ OK — no fix needed.

[INT-007] PRO AGENT compact.md IGNORED, BUT system.md IS TRACKED
  .gitignore has:
    agentin/agents/pro/*/memory/compact.md
  All pro agent system.md files are tracked (intentional — these are templates).
  ✅ OK — no fix needed.

[INT-008] PLUGIN STATE — PARTIAL COVERAGE
  .gitignore has:
    agentin/plugins/agent-rag-studio/data/state.json
    agentin/plugins/http-tts-bridge/runtime/
  But the RAG studio's data directory also contains:
    agentin/plugins/agent-rag-studio/data/tech-support-menu-20.json  ← tracked
  This looks like user-uploaded RAG dataset data. Should it be in VCS?
  Also, no general rule for plugin runtime data exists — any new plugin that
  writes to its own data/ or runtime/ directory will leak into git.

  Fix — add general plugin runtime rules:
    agentin/plugins/*/data/*.json
    !agentin/plugins/*/data/state.default.json
    agentin/plugins/*/runtime/


