────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CATEGORY 5 — .gitignore GAPS & MISSING RULES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[INT-011] NO GLOBAL __pycache__ OR *.pyc RULE
  .gitignore only covers specific paths. Python bytecode files are not globally
  ignored. Any future Python plugin will leak .pyc files.

  Fix:
    __pycache__/
    *.pyc
    *.pyo

[INT-012] NO RULE FOR agentin/a2a/
  The entire A2A runtime directory (events, tasks, targets) is unmentioned
  in .gitignore. See INT-002.

[INT-013] NO RULE FOR agentin/tasks/
  The tasks directory is runtime state. Not in .gitignore.

[INT-014] NO RULE FOR RUNTIME SUB-AGENTS
  agentin/agents/sub/ has no .gitignore coverage for runtime-spawned agents.
  Only the template sub-agents should be tracked.

[INT-015] ISSUE FILES THEMSELVES (code.issues, ui.issues, integrity.issues)
  These audit files are currently showing as untracked:
    ?? code.issues
    ?? ui.issues
  Decision: track them as project documentation, or ignore them.
  If you want them private:
    *.issues

[INT-016] NO GLOBAL RULE FOR DEVELOPMENT ARTIFACTS
  Files like *.issues, TODO.md, SCRATCH.*, etc. have no blanket ignore rule.
  Add if you use them:
    *.issues
    SCRATCH.*
    TODO.md


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CATEGORY 6 — SENSITIVE CONTENT EXPOSURE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[INT-017] .env IS CORRECTLY IGNORED — BUT .env.example IS IDENTICAL
  .env is in .gitignore ✅
  .env.example is tracked and contains the same structure with empty values.
  This is the correct pattern. However, verify that your actual .env file
  hasn't been accidentally committed in the past:
    git log --all --diff-filter=A --summary -- ".env"
  Result: no .env commit found. ✅ Safe.

[INT-018] TELEGRAM BOT TOKEN IN CONNECTOR FILES
  Path: agentin/connectors/telegram-bot.js
        agentin/connectors/telegram-relay.js
  These files are tracked. Verify they don't contain hardcoded tokens.
  The token should come from .env (TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN), not from the file.
  If either file has a token value, it's exposed in git history forever.

[INT-019] A2A TARGET CONFIGS MAY CONTAIN ENDPOINTS
  Path: agentin/a2a/targets/codex.json
        agentin/a2a/targets/comfyui.json
        agentin/a2a/targets/lmstudio.json
  These may contain local network addresses, ports, or API URLs that reveal
  your infrastructure. Not a secret per se, but potentially sensitive.

[INT-020] PLUGIN config.txt TRACKED
  Path: agentin/plugins/http-tts-bridge/config.txt
  If this contains local paths, ports, or any user-specific configuration,
  it will be pushed. Check its contents.


────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CATEGORY 7 — GIT WORKFLOW RECOMMENDATIONS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[INT-021] USE git rm --cached FOR ALREADY-TRACKED FILES
  Adding a path to .gitignore does NOT untrack files already in the index.
  You must run `git rm -r --cached <path>` first, then commit.
  Do this for all files flagged in INT-001 through INT-005.

[INT-022] CONSIDER A PRE-COMMIT HOOK
  To prevent accidental commits of sensitive files, add a pre-commit hook:
    .git/hooks/pre-commit:
    #!/bin/sh
    # Block commits containing .env, .db, .pyc, or pycache
    if git diff --cached --name-only | grep -qE '\.env$|\.db$|\.pyc$|__pycache__'; then
      echo "ERROR: Attempting to commit sensitive/generated files"
      exit 1
    fi

[INT-023] CONSIDER .gitattributes FOR BINARY FILES
  The artifacts-icon.svg and any future binary assets should have:
    *.svg binary
    *.png binary
    *.ico binary
  This prevents git from trying to merge/diff them as text.


================================================================================
RECOMMENDED .gitignore ADDITIONS (copy-paste block)
================================================================================

Paste this at the end of your current .gitignore:

# ===== PYTHON BUILD ARTIFACTS =====
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# ===== A2A RUNTIME DATA =====
agentin/a2a/events/
agentin/a2a/tasks/
# Uncomment if targets are also runtime-generated:
# agentin/a2a/targets/

# ===== RUNTIME SUB-AGENTS =====
# Keep template sub-agents, ignore timestamped runtime ones
agentin/agents/sub/diag-*/
agentin/agents/sub/live-search-verifier-[0-9]*/
agentin/agents/sub/live-time-verifier-[0-9]*/

# ===== TASK QUEUE STATE =====
agentin/tasks/

# ===== PLUGIN RUNTIME DATA (general) =====
agentin/plugins/*/runtime/
# Uncomment to ignore all plugin data except defaults:
# agentin/plugins/*/data/*.json
# !agentin/plugins/*/data/state.default.json

# ===== AUDIT/ISSUE FILES (optional) =====
# *.issues


================================================================================
CLEANUP COMMANDS (run once after updating .gitignore)
================================================================================

  # 1. Remove tracked __pycache__ files
  git rm -r --cached agentin/plugins/http-tts-bridge/python_backend/backend/__pycache__/
  git rm -r --cached agentin/plugins/http-tts-bridge/python_backend/backend/routers/__pycache__/

  # 2. Remove A2A runtime data
  git rm -r --cached agentin/a2a/events/
  git rm -r --cached agentin/a2a/tasks/

  # 3. Remove runtime sub-agents
  git rm -r --cached "agentin/agents/sub/diag-search-1776453748776/"
  git rm -r --cached "agentin/agents/sub/live-search-verifier-1776453564659/"
  git rm -r --cached "agentin/agents/sub/live-search-verifier-1776453628736/"
  git rm -r --cached "agentin/agents/sub/live-time-verifier-1776454130153/"
  git rm -r --cached "agentin/agents/sub/live-time-verifier-1776454985119/"
  git rm -r --cached "agentin/agents/sub/live-time-verifier-1776455978209/"
  git rm -r --cached "agentin/agents/sub/live-time-verifier-1776457715692/"

  # 4. Remove task queue state
  git rm --cached agentin/tasks/tasks.md

  # 5. Remove workflow duplicates
  git rm --cached agentin/workflows/system_health_check_copy.json

  # 6. Commit the cleanup
  git add .gitignore
  git commit -m "chore: untrack runtime files, fix .gitignore coverage"


